1. Download VirtualBox for your platform (https://www.virtualbox.org/wiki/Downloads)
2. Install VirtualBox (defaults should be acceptable)
3. Download the Ubuntu 12.10 64-bit ISO (http://www.ubuntu.com/download/desktop/thank-you?release=latest&bits=64&distro=desktop&status=zeroc)
4. Create your Ubuntu VM
   a. Start up VirtualBox
   b. Click the "new" button in the top-left corner
   c. Put "Era of Kings dev" or something similar in the name field
   d. Choose "Linux" and "Ubuntu (64-bit)" from the drop-down menus
   e. Click next
   f. Choose a memory size that seems reasonable and click next
